Three people died today morning in Tanzania's capital dar es salaam after a gunman opened fire near the french embassy. Two police officers were among those killed in the incident with police saying that the 29-year-old suspect was also killed. According to Tanzanian police, the lone gunman was identified as hamza Hassan Mohammed and was on a robbery mission. The attacker carried out the attack using an AK 47 rifle outside the french embassy, where he had been spotted controlling traffic on the Ali Hassan Mwinyi road. Tanzania&rsquo;s inspector general of police Simon Sirro said the suspect had earlier opened fire on police officers who were responding to distress calls by passers-by. The attack occurred shortly after president Samia Suluhu Hassan addressed security officials in another part of the city.